# What are the implications of increasing dissent among municipal deputies in Russia?

## Summary
Increasing dissent among municipal deputies in Russia is becoming more and more vocal, with nearly 50 deputies in Moscow, St. Petersburg and Kolpino having signed a petition demanding President Vladimir Putin's resignation <font color=#FF3399>[1]</font>. Further, four deputies from Moscow's Smolninskoye municipality were recently summoned by police for "discrediting of the ruling establishment" <font color=#FF3399>[2]</font>. In a rare display of dissent in Russia, the deputies appealed to the Russian Duma to impeach Putin for what they called crimes of high treason <font color=#FF3399>[3]</font>. Furthermore, in the Kharkiv region, deputies from St Petersburg's Smolninsky District issued a statement calling for Mr Putin to be tried for treason, which was supported by most of the district's deputies <font color=#FF3399>[4, 5]</font>. Thus, it is evident that the growing dissent among municipal deputies in Russia is having serious implications for the future of the country.

